description:
&lt;p&gt;Bradford District Care NHS Foundation Trust’s Hub Teams are multi-disciplined teams of administrators dealing with enquiries from patients, service users, carers and clinicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is delivered in a defined community based Administration Hub and Inpatient Area setting which is a 5 day per week service operating core office hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Administrator role will provide efficient, effective and high quality clerical support to a range of identified professionals within clinical services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be a part of a growing team and the role would be ideal for those with experience of patient and service user contact, an excellent telephone manner, dictation typing experience and a strong administration focus. Comprehensive training can be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 Permanent roles, 36 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 11th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short listing date 13th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date 23th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Gemma Pinder&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Inpatients Administration Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: gemma.pinder@bdct.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:07701280167 or 01274 228588&lt;/p&gt;
